      "popup": "<div style=\"max-width:300px;font-family:'Crimson Text',serif\"><h3 style=\"color:#90A4AE;margin:0 0 6px;font-size:14px\">Interior Low Plateaus Karst</h3><p style=\"font-size:12px;color:#78909C\">Mississippian-age limestone, ~150 m thick. Home to Mammoth Cave System (580+ km), Salts Cave, and dozens of other major systems. The densest concentration of long cave systems in the world relative to the thickness of the host rock. South-central Kentucky through north-central Tennessee.</p><p style=\"font-size:11px;color:#607D8B\">Bedrock: Mississippian limestone (Ste. Genevieve, St. Louis formations)</p></div>",
