      "popup": "<div style=\"max-width:300px;font-family:'Crimson Text',serif\"><h3 style=\"color:#90A4AE;margin:0 0 6px;font-size:14px\">Tennessee Valley / Highland Rim Karst</h3><p style=\"font-size:12px;color:#78909C\">Limestone bluffs along the Tennessee River and its tributaries in NW Alabama and south-central Tennessee. Host to Dust Cave, Stanfield-Worley, Russell Cave. Tennessee has more recorded caves (10,000+) than any other state.</p><p style=\"font-size:11px;color:#607D8B\">Bedrock: Mississippian & Ordovician limestone and dolomite</p></div>",
