      "popup": "<div style=\"max-width:300px;font-family:'Crimson Text',serif\"><h3 style=\"color:#90A4AE;margin:0 0 6px;font-size:14px\">Appalachian Valley & Ridge / Plateau Karst</h3><p style=\"font-size:12px;color:#78909C\">Extends from central Alabama to New York. The Valley and Ridge has extensive karst in Cambrian-Ordovician carbonates of the Great Valley. The Appalachian Plateaus contain world-class karst in the Mississippian Greenbrier Group (WV). Host to Meadowcroft Rockshelter, Russell Cave, and thousands of documented caves.</p><p style=\"font-size:11px;color:#607D8B\">Bedrock: Cambrian-Devonian carbonates (Valley & Ridge); Mississippian limestone (Plateaus)</p></div>",
      "popupOptions": {
        "maxWidth": 320
      },
