      "popup": "<div style=\"max-width:300px;font-family:'Crimson Text',serif\"><h3 style=\"color:#90A4AE;margin:0 0 6px;font-size:14px\">Ozark Plateau Karst</h3><p style=\"font-size:12px;color:#78909C\">Extensive karst on limestones ringing the Ozark Dome across Missouri, northern Arkansas, and eastern Oklahoma. Missouri has 7,300+ recorded caves (second only to Tennessee). Host to Graham Cave, Rodgers Shelter, and thousands of springs. The Springfield and Salem Plateaus are the primary karst zones.</p><p style=\"font-size:11px;color:#607D8B\">Bedrock: Ordovician dolomite and Mississippian limestone</p></div>",
